80static bucket *
81lookup_type_destructor(char *tag)
82{
83 const char fmt[] = "%.*s destructor";
84 char name[1024] = "\0";
85 bucket *bp, **bpp = &default_destructor[TYPE_SPECIFIED];
86
87 while ((bp = *bpp) != NULL)
88 {
89 if (bp->tag == tag)
90 return (bp);
91 bpp = &bp->link;
92 }
93
94 sprintf(name, fmt, (int)(sizeof(name) - sizeof(fmt)), tag);
95 *bpp = bp = make_bucket(name);
96 bp->tag = tag;
97
98 return (bp);
99}
100#endif /* defined(YYBTYACC) */

102static void
103cachec(int c)
104{
105 assert(cinc >= 0);
106 if (cinc >= cache_size)
107 {
108 cache_size += CACHE_SIZE;
109 cache = TREALLOC(char, cache, cache_size);
110 NO_SPACE(cache);
111 }
112 cache[cinc] = (char)c;
113 ++cinc;
114}

116typedef enum
117{
118 ldSPC1,
119 ldSPC2,
120 ldNAME,
121 ldSPC3,
122 ldNUM,
123 ldSPC4,
124 ldFILE,
125 ldOK,
126 ldERR
127}
128LINE_DIR;
129
130/*
131 * Expect this pattern:
132 * /^[[:space:]]*#[[:space:]]*
133 * line[[:space:]]+
134 * [[:digit:]]+
135 * ([[:space:]]*|[[:space:]]+"[^"]+")/
136 */
137static int
138line_directive(void)
139{
140#define UNLESS(what) if (what) { ld = ldERR; break; }
141 int n;
142 int line_1st = -1;
143 int name_1st = -1;
144 int name_end = -1;
145 LINE_DIR ld = ldSPC1;
146 for (n = 0; (ld <= ldOK) && (line[n] != '\0'); ++n)
147 {
148 int ch = UCH(line[n]);
149 switch (ld)
150 {
151 case ldSPC1:
152 if (isspace(UCH(ch)))
153 {
154 break;
155 }
156 else
157 UNLESS(ch != '#');
158 ld = ldSPC2;
159 break;
160 case ldSPC2:
161 if (isspace(UCH(ch)))
162 {
163 break;
164 }
165 /* FALLTHRU */
166 case ldNAME:
167 UNLESS(strncmp(line + n, "line", 4));
168 n += 4;
169 if (line[n] == '\0')
170 {
171 ld = ldOK;
172 break;
173 }
174 else
175 UNLESS(!isspace(UCH(line[n])));
176 ld = ldSPC3;
177 break;
178 case ldSPC3:
179 if (isspace(UCH(ch)))
180 {
181 break;
182 }
183 else
184 UNLESS(!isdigit(UCH(ch)));
185 line_1st = n;
186 ld = ldNUM;
187 /* FALLTHRU */
188 case ldNUM:
189 if (isdigit(UCH(ch)))
190 {
191 break;
192 }
193 else
194 UNLESS(!isspace(UCH(ch)));
195 ld = ldSPC4;
196 break;
197 case ldSPC4:
198 if (isspace(UCH(ch)))
199 {
200 break;
201 }
202 else
203 UNLESS(ch != '"');
204 UNLESS(line[n + 1] == '"');
205 ld = ldFILE;
206 name_1st = n;
207 break;
208 case ldFILE:
209 if (ch != '"')
210 {
211 break;
212 }
213 ld = ldOK;
214 name_end = n;
215 /* FALLTHRU */
216 case ldERR:
217 case ldOK:
218 break;
219 }
220 }
221
222 if (ld == ldOK)
223 {
224 size_t need = (size_t) (name_end - name_1st);
225 if ((long)need > (long)input_file_name_len)
226 {
227 input_file_name_len = ((need + 1) * 3) / 2;
228 input_file_name = TREALLOC(char, input_file_name, input_file_name_len);
229 NO_SPACE(input_file_name);
230 }
231 if ((long)need > 0)
232 {
233 memcpy(input_file_name, line + name_1st + 1, need - 1);
234 input_file_name[need - 1] = '\0';
235 }
236 else
237 {
238 input_file_name[0] = '\0';
239 }
240 }
241
242 if (ld >= ldNUM && ld < ldERR)
243 {
244 if (line_1st >= 0)
245 {
246 lineno = (int)strtol(line + line_1st, NULL, 10) - 1;
247 }
248 else
249 {
250 lineno = 0;
251 }
252 }
253
254 return (ld == ldOK);
255#undef UNLESS
256}

258static void
259get_line(void)
260{
261 FILE *f = input_file;
262 int c;
263 int i;
264
265 do
266 {
267 if (saw_eof || (c = getc(f)) == EOF)
268 {
269 if (line)
270 {
271 FREE(line);
272 line = 0;
273 }
274 cptr = 0;
275 saw_eof = 1;
276 return;
277 }
278
279 if (line == NULL || linesize != (LINESIZE + 1))
280 {
281 if (line)
282 FREE(line);
283 linesize = LINESIZE + 1;
284 line = TMALLOC(char, linesize);
285 NO_SPACE(line);
286 }
287
288 i = 0;
289 ++lineno;
290 for (;;)
291 {
292 line[i++] = (char)c;
293 if (c == '\n')
294 break;
295 if ((i + 3) >= linesize)
296 {
297 linesize += LINESIZE;
298 line = TREALLOC(char, line, linesize);
299 NO_SPACE(line);
300 }
301 c = getc(f);
302 if (c == EOF)
303 {
304 line[i++] = '\n';
305 saw_eof = 1;
306 break;
307 }
308 }
309 line[i] = '\0';
310 }
311 while (line_directive());
312 cptr = line;
313 return;
314}

316static char *
317dup_line(void)
318{
319 char *p, *s, *t;
320
321 if (line == NULL)
322 return (NULL);
323 s = line;
324 while (*s != '\n')
325 ++s;
326 p = TMALLOC(char, s - line + 1);
327 NO_SPACE(p);
328
329 s = line;
330 t = p;
331 while ((*t++ = *s++) != '\n')
332 continue;
333 return (p);
334}

336static void
337skip_comment(void)
338{
339 char *s;
340 struct ainfo a;
341 a.a_lineno = lineno;
342 a.a_line = dup_line();
343 a.a_cptr = a.a_line + (cptr - line);
344
345 s = cptr + 2;
346 for (;;)
347 {
348 if (*s == '*' && s[1] == '/')
349 {
350 cptr = s + 2;
351 FREE(a.a_line);
352 return;
353 }
354 if (*s == '\n')
355 {
356 get_line();
357 if (line == NULL)
358 unterminated_comment(&a);
359 s = cptr;
360 }
361 else
362 ++s;
363 }
364}

366static int
367next_inline(void)
368{
369 char *s;
370
371 if (line == NULL)
372 {
373 get_line();
374 if (line == NULL)
375 return (EOF);
376 }
377
378 s = cptr;
379 for (;;)
380 {
381 switch (*s)
382 {
383 case '/':
384 if (s[1] == '*')
385 {
386 cptr = s;
387 skip_comment();
388 s = cptr;
389 break;
390 }
391 else if (s[1] == '/')
392 {
393 get_line();
394 if (line == NULL)
395 return (EOF);
396 s = cptr;
397 break;
398 }
399 /* FALLTHRU */
400
401 default:
402 cptr = s;
403 return (*s);
404 }
405 }
406}

408static int
409nextc(void)
410{
411 int ch;
412 int finish = 0;
413
414 do
415 {
416 switch (ch = next_inline())
417 {
418 case '\n':
419 get_line();
420 break;
421 case ' ':
422 case '\t':
423 case '\f':
424 case '\r':
425 case '\v':
426 case ',':
427 case ';':
428 ++cptr;
429 break;
430 case '\\':
431 ch = '%';
432 /* FALLTHRU */
433 default:
434 finish = 1;
435 break;
436 }
437 }
438 while (!finish);
439
440 return ch;
441}

480static int
481compare_keys(const void *a, const void *b)
482{
483 const struct keyword *p = (const struct keyword *)a;
484 const struct keyword *q = (const struct keyword *)b;
485 return strcmp(p->name, q->name);
486}

488static int
489keyword(void)
490{
491 int c;
492 char *t_cptr = cptr;
493 struct keyword *key;
494
495 c = *++cptr;
496 if (isalpha(UCH(c)))
497 {
498 cinc = 0;
499 for (;;)
500 {
501 if (isalpha(UCH(c)))
502 {
503 if (isupper(UCH(c)))
504 c = tolower(c);
505 cachec(c);
506 }
507 else if (isdigit(UCH(c))
508 || c == '-'
509 || c == '.'
510 || c == '$')
511 {
512 cachec(c);
513 }
514 else if (c == '_')
515 {
516 /* treat keywords spelled with '_' as if it were '-' */
517 cachec('-');
518 }
519 else
520 {
521 break;
522 }
523 c = *++cptr;
524 }
525 cachec(NUL);
526
527 if ((key = bsearch(cache, keywords,
528 sizeof(keywords) / sizeof(*key),
529 sizeof(*key), compare_keys)))
530 return key->token;
531 }
532 else
533 {
534 ++cptr;
535 if (c == L_CURL)
536 return (TEXT);
537 if (c == '%' || c == '\\')
538 return (MARK);
539 if (c == '<')
540 return (LEFT);
541 if (c == '>')
542 return (RIGHT);
543 if (c == '0')
544 return (TOKEN);
545 if (c == '2')
546 return (NONASSOC);
547 }
548 syntax_error(lineno, line, t_cptr);
549 /*NOTREACHED */
550}

584static char *
585copy_string(int quote)
586{
587 struct mstring *temp = msnew();
588 int c;
589 struct ainfo a;
590 a.a_lineno = lineno;
591 a.a_line = dup_line();
592 a.a_cptr = a.a_line + (cptr - line - 1);
593
594 for (;;)
595 {
596 c = *cptr++;
597 mputc(temp, c);
598 if (c == quote)
599 {
600 FREE(a.a_line);
601 return msdone(temp);
602 }
603 if (c == '\n')
604 unterminated_string(&a);
605 if (c == '\\')
606 {
607 c = *cptr++;
608 mputc(temp, c);
609 if (c == '\n')
610 {
611 get_line();
612 if (line == NULL)
613 unterminated_string(&a);
614 }
615 }
616 }
617}

619static char *
620copy_comment(void)
621{
622 struct mstring *temp = msnew();
623 int c;
624
625 c = *cptr;
626 if (c == '/')
627 {
628 mputc(temp, '*');
629 while ((c = *++cptr) != '\n')
630 {
631 mputc(temp, c);
632 if (c == '*' && cptr[1] == '/')
633 mputc(temp, ' ');
634 }
635 mputc(temp, '*');
636 mputc(temp, '/');
637 }
638 else if (c == '*')
639 {
640 struct ainfo a;
641 a.a_lineno = lineno;
642 a.a_line = dup_line();
643 a.a_cptr = a.a_line + (cptr - line - 1);
644
645 mputc(temp, c);
646 ++cptr;
647 for (;;)
648 {
649 c = *cptr++;
650 mputc(temp, c);
651 if (c == '*' && *cptr == '/')
652 {
653 mputc(temp, '/');
654 ++cptr;
655 FREE(a.a_line);
656 return msdone(temp);
657 }
658 if (c == '\n')
659 {
660 get_line();
661 if (line == NULL)
662 unterminated_comment(&a);
663 }
664 }
665 }
666 return msdone(temp);
667}

669static void
670copy_text(void)
671{
672 int c;
673 FILE *f = text_file;
674 int need_newline = 0;
675 struct ainfo a;
676 a.a_lineno = lineno;
677 a.a_line = dup_line();
678 a.a_cptr = a.a_line + (cptr - line - 2);
679
680 if (*cptr == '\n')
681 {
682 get_line();
683 if (line == NULL)
684 unterminated_text(&a);
685 }
686 if (!lflag)
687 fprintf(f, line_format, lineno, input_file_name);
688
689 loop:
690 c = *cptr++;
691 switch (c)
692 {
693 case '\n':
694 putc('\n', f);
695 need_newline = 0;
696 get_line();
697 if (line)
698 goto loop;
699 unterminated_text(&a);
700
701 case '\'':
702 case '"':
703 putc(c, f);
704 {
705 char *s = copy_string(c);
706 fputs(s, f);
707 free(s);
708 }
709 need_newline = 1;
710 goto loop;
711
712 case '/':
713 putc(c, f);
714 {
715 char *s = copy_comment();
716 fputs(s, f);
717 free(s);
718 }
719 need_newline = 1;
720 goto loop;
721
722 case '%':
723 case '\\':
724 if (*cptr == R_CURL)
725 {
726 if (need_newline)
727 putc('\n', f);
728 ++cptr;
729 FREE(a.a_line);
730 return;
731 }
732 /* FALLTHRU */
733
734 default:
735 putc(c, f);
736 need_newline = 1;
737 goto loop;
738 }
739}

757static void
758copy_union(void)
759{
760 int c;
761 int depth;
762 struct ainfo a;
763 a.a_lineno = lineno;
764 a.a_line = dup_line();
765 a.a_cptr = a.a_line + (cptr - line - 6);
766
767 if (unionized)
768 over_unionized(cptr - 6);
769 unionized = 1;
770
771 puts_both("#ifdef YYSTYPE\n");
772 puts_both("#undef YYSTYPE_IS_DECLARED\n");
773 puts_both("#define YYSTYPE_IS_DECLARED 1\n");
774 puts_both("#endif\n");
775 puts_both("#ifndef YYSTYPE_IS_DECLARED\n");
776 puts_both("#define YYSTYPE_IS_DECLARED 1\n");
777
778 if (!lflag)
779 fprintf(text_file, line_format, lineno, input_file_name);
780 puts_both("typedef union");
781
782 depth = 0;
783 loop:
784 c = *cptr++;
785 putc_both(c);
786 switch (c)
787 {
788 case '\n':
789 get_line();
790 if (line == NULL)
791 unterminated_union(&a);
792 goto loop;
793
794 case L_CURL:
795 ++depth;
796 goto loop;
797
798 case R_CURL:
799 if (--depth == 0)
800 {
801 puts_both(" YYSTYPE;\n");
802 puts_both("#endif /* !YYSTYPE_IS_DECLARED */\n");
803 FREE(a.a_line);
804 return;
805 }
806 goto loop;
807
808 case '\'':
809 case '"':
810 {
811 char *s = copy_string(c);
812 puts_both(s);
813 free(s);
814 }
815 goto loop;
816
817 case '/':
818 {
819 char *s = copy_comment();
820 puts_both(s);
821 free(s);
822 }
823 goto loop;
824
825 default:
826 goto loop;
827 }
828}

830static char *
831after_blanks(char *s)
832{
833 while (*s != '\0' && isspace(UCH(*s)))
834 ++s;
835 return s;
836}
837
838/*
839 * Trim leading/trailing blanks, and collapse multiple embedded blanks to a
840 * single space. Return index to last character in the buffer.
841 */
842static int
843trim_blanks(char *buffer)
844{
845 if (*buffer != '\0')
846 {
847 char *d = buffer;
848 char *s = after_blanks(d);
849
850 while ((*d++ = *s++) != '\0')
851 {
852 ;
853 }
854
855 --d;
856 while ((--d != buffer) && isspace(UCH(*d)))
857 *d = '\0';
858
859 for (s = d = buffer; (*d++ = *s++) != '\0';)
860 {
861 if (isspace(UCH(*s)))
862 {
863 *s = ' ';
864 while (isspace(UCH(*s)))
865 {
866 *s++ = ' ';
867 }
868 --s;
869 }
870 }
871 }
872
873 return (int)strlen(buffer) - 1;
874}

876/*
877 * Scan forward in the current line-buffer looking for a right-curly bracket.
878 *
879 * Parameters begin with a left-curly bracket, and continue until there are no
880 * more interesting characters after the last right-curly bracket on the
881 * current line. Bison documents parameters as separated like this:
882 * {type param1} {type2 param2}
883 * but also accepts commas (although some versions of bison mishandle this)
884 * {type param1, type2 param2}
885 */
886static int
887more_curly(void)
888{
889 char *save = cptr;
890 int result = 0;
891 int finish = 0;
892 do
893 {
894 switch (next_inline())
895 {
896 case 0:
897 case '\n':
898 finish = 1;
899 break;
900 case R_CURL:
901 finish = 1;
902 result = 1;
903 break;
904 }
905 ++cptr;
906 }
907 while (!finish);
908 cptr = save;
909 return result;
910}

912static void
913save_param(int k, char *buffer, int name, int type2)
914{
915 param *head, *p;
916
917 p = TMALLOC(param, 1);
918 NO_SPACE(p);
919
920 p->type2 = strdup(buffer + type2);
921 NO_SPACE(p->type2);
922 buffer[type2] = '\0';
923 (void)trim_blanks(p->type2);
924
925 p->name = strdup(buffer + name);
926 NO_SPACE(p->name);
927 buffer[name] = '\0';
928 (void)trim_blanks(p->name);
929
930 p->type = strdup(buffer);
931 NO_SPACE(p->type);
932 (void)trim_blanks(p->type);
933
934 if (k == LEX_PARAM)
935 head = lex_param;
936 else
937 head = parse_param;
938
939 if (head != NULL)
940 {
941 while (head->next)
942 head = head->next;
943 head->next = p;
944 }
945 else
946 {
947 if (k == LEX_PARAM)
948 lex_param = p;
949 else
950 parse_param = p;
951 }
952 p->next = NULL;
953}

955/*
956 * Keep a linked list of parameters. This may be multi-line, if the trailing
957 * right-curly bracket is absent.
958 */
959static void
960copy_param(int k)
961{
962 int c;
963 int name, type2;
964 int curly = 0;
965 char *buf = 0;
966 int i = -1;
967 size_t buf_size = 0;
968 int st_lineno = lineno;
969 char *comma;
970
971 do
972 {
973 int state = curly;
974 c = next_inline();
975 switch (c)
976 {
977 case EOF:
978 unexpected_EOF();
979 break;
980 case L_CURL:
981 if (curly == 1)
982 {
983 goto oops;
984 }
985 curly = 1;
986 st_lineno = lineno;
987 break;
988 case R_CURL:
989 if (curly != 1)
990 {
991 goto oops;
992 }
993 curly = 2;
994 break;
995 case '\n':
996 if (curly == 0)
997 {
998 goto oops;
999 }
1000 break;
1001 case '%':
1002 if ((curly == 1) && (cptr == line))
1003 {
1004 lineno = st_lineno;
1005 missing_brace();
1006 }
1007 /* FALLTHRU */
1008 case '"':
1009 case '\'':
1010 goto oops;
1011 default:
1012 if (curly == 0 && !isspace(UCH(c)))
1013 {
1014 goto oops;
1015 }
1016 break;
1017 }
1018 if (buf == 0)
1019 {
1020 buf_size = (size_t) linesize;
1021 buf = TMALLOC(char, buf_size);
1022 }
1023 else if (c == '\n')
1024 {
1025 get_line();
1026 if (line == NULL)
1027 unexpected_EOF();
1028 --cptr;
1029 buf_size += (size_t) linesize;
1030 buf = TREALLOC(char, buf, buf_size);
1031 }
1032 NO_SPACE(buf);
1033 if (curly)
1034 {
1035 if ((state == 2) && (c == L_CURL))
1036 {
1037 buf[++i] = ',';
1038 }
1039 else if ((state == 2) && isspace(UCH(c)))
1040 {
1041 ;
1042 }
1043 else if ((c != L_CURL) && (c != R_CURL))
1044 {
1045 buf[++i] = (char)c;
1046 }
1047 }
1048 cptr++;
1049 }
1050 while (curly < 2 || more_curly());
1051
1052 if (i == 0)
1053 {
1054 if (curly == 1)
1055 {
1056 lineno = st_lineno;
1057 missing_brace();
1058 }
1059 goto oops;
1060 }
1061
1062 buf[++i] = '\0';
1063 (void)trim_blanks(buf);
1064
1065 comma = buf - 1;
1066 do
1067 {
1068 char *parms = (comma + 1);
1069 comma = strchr(parms, ',');
1070 if (comma != 0)
1071 *comma = '\0';
1072
1073 (void)trim_blanks(parms);
1074 i = (int)strlen(parms) - 1;
1075 if (i < 0)
1076 {
1077 goto oops;
1078 }
1079
1080 if (parms[i] == ']')
1081 {
1082 int level = 1;
1083 while (i >= 0 && level > 0 && parms[i] != '[')
1084 {
1085 if (parms[i] == ']')
1086 ++level;
1087 else if (parms[i] == '[')
1088 --level;
1089 i--;
1090 }
1091 if (i <= 0)
1092 unexpected_EOF();
1093 type2 = i--;
1094 }
1095 else
1096 {
1097 type2 = i + 1;
1098 }
1099
1100 while (i > 0 && (isalnum(UCH(parms[i])) || UCH(parms[i]) == '_'))
1101 i--;
1102
1103 if (!isspace(UCH(parms[i])) && parms[i] != '*')
1104 goto oops;
1105
1106 name = i + 1;
1107
1108 save_param(k, parms, name, type2);
1109 }
1110 while (comma != 0);
1111 FREE(buf);
1112 return;
1113
1114 oops:
1115 FREE(buf);
1116 syntax_error(lineno, line, cptr);
1117}

1119static int
1120hexval(int c)
1121{
1122 if (c >= '0' && c <= '9')
1123 return (c - '0');
1124 if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'F')
1125 return (c - 'A' + 10);
1126 if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'f')
1127 return (c - 'a' + 10);
1128 return (-1);
1129}

1131static bucket *
1132get_literal(void)
1133{
1134 int c, quote;
1135 int i;
1136 int n;
1137 char *s;
1138 bucket *bp;
1139 struct ainfo a;
1140 a.a_lineno = lineno;
1141 a.a_line = dup_line();
1142 a.a_cptr = a.a_line + (cptr - line);
1143
1144 quote = *cptr++;
1145 cinc = 0;
1146 for (;;)
1147 {
1148 c = *cptr++;
1149 if (c == quote)
1150 break;
1151 if (c == '\n')
1152 unterminated_string(&a);
1153 if (c == '\\')
1154 {
1155 char *c_cptr = cptr - 1;
1156
1157 c = *cptr++;
1158 switch (c)
1159 {
1160 case '\n':
1161 get_line();
1162 if (line == NULL)
1163 unterminated_string(&a);
1164 continue;
1165
1166 case '0':
1167 case '1':
1168 case '2':
1169 case '3':
1170 case '4':
1171 case '5':
1172 case '6':
1173 case '7':
1174 n = c - '0';
1175 c = *cptr;
1176 if (IS_OCTAL(c))
1177 {
1178 n = (n << 3) + (c - '0');
1179 c = *++cptr;
1180 if (IS_OCTAL(c))
1181 {
1182 n = (n << 3) + (c - '0');
1183 ++cptr;
1184 }
1185 }
1186 if (n > MAXCHAR)
1187 illegal_character(c_cptr);
1188 c = n;
1189 break;
1190
1191 case 'x':
1192 c = *cptr++;
1193 n = hexval(c);
1194 if (n < 0 || n >= 16)
1195 illegal_character(c_cptr);
1196 for (;;)
1197 {
1198 c = *cptr;
1199 i = hexval(c);
1200 if (i < 0 || i >= 16)
1201 break;
1202 ++cptr;
1203 n = (n << 4) + i;
1204 if (n > MAXCHAR)
1205 illegal_character(c_cptr);
1206 }
1207 c = n;
1208 break;
1209
1210 case 'a':
1211 c = 7;
1212 break;
1213 case 'b':
1214 c = '\b';
1215 break;
1216 case 'f':
1217 c = '\f';
1218 break;
1219 case 'n':
1220 c = '\n';
1221 break;
1222 case 'r':
1223 c = '\r';
1224 break;
1225 case 't':
1226 c = '\t';
1227 break;
1228 case 'v':
1229 c = '\v';
1230 break;
1231 }
1232 }
1233 cachec(c);
1234 }
1235 FREE(a.a_line);
1236
1237 n = cinc;
1238 s = TMALLOC(char, n);
1239 NO_SPACE(s);
1240
1241 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i)
1242 s[i] = cache[i];
1243
1244 cinc = 0;
1245 if (n == 1)
1246 cachec('\'');
1247 else
1248 cachec('"');
1249
1250 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i)
1251 {
1252 c = UCH(s[i]);
1253 if (c == '\\' || c == cache[0])
1254 {
1255 cachec('\\');
1256 cachec(c);
1257 }
1258 else if (isprint(UCH(c)))
1259 cachec(c);
1260 else
1261 {
1262 cachec('\\');
1263 switch (c)
1264 {
1265 case 7:
1266 cachec('a');
1267 break;
1268 case '\b':
1269 cachec('b');
1270 break;
1271 case '\f':
1272 cachec('f');
1273 break;
1274 case '\n':
1275 cachec('n');
1276 break;
1277 case '\r':
1278 cachec('r');
1279 break;
1280 case '\t':
1281 cachec('t');
1282 break;
1283 case '\v':
1284 cachec('v');
1285 break;
1286 default:
1287 cachec(((c >> 6) & 7) + '0');
1288 cachec(((c >> 3) & 7) + '0');
1289 cachec((c & 7) + '0');
1290 break;
1291 }
1292 }
1293 }
1294
1295 if (n == 1)
1296 cachec('\'');
1297 else
1298 cachec('"');
1299
1300 cachec(NUL);
1301 bp = lookup(cache);
1302 bp->class = TERM;
1303 if (n == 1 && bp->value == UNDEFINED)
1304 bp->value = UCH(*s);
1305 FREE(s);
1306
1307 return (bp);
1308}

1310static int
1311is_reserved(char *name)
1312{
1313 char *s;
1314
1315 if (strcmp(name, ".") == 0 ||
1316 strcmp(name, "$accept") == 0 ||
1317 strcmp(name, "$end") == 0)
1318 return (1);
1319
1320 if (name[0] == '$' && name[1] == '$' && isdigit(UCH(name[2])))
1321 {
1322 s = name + 3;
1323 while (isdigit(UCH(*s)))

1328
1329 return (0);

1369static char *
1370cache_tag(char *tag, size_t len)
1371{
1372 int i;
1373 char *s;
1374
1375 for (i = 0; i < ntags; ++i)
1376 {
1377 if (strncmp(tag, tag_table[i], len) == 0 &&
1378 tag_table[i][len] == NUL)
1379 return (tag_table[i]);
1380 }
1381
1382 if (ntags >= tagmax)
1383 {
1384 tagmax += 16;

1386 (tag_table

1401static char *
1402get_tag(void)
1403{
1404 int c;

1406 char *t_line = dup_line();
1407 char *t_cptr = t_line + (cptr - line);
1408
1409 ++cptr;

1411 if (c == EOF)
1412 unexpected_EOF();
1413 if (!IS_NAME1(c))
1414 illegal_tag(t_lineno, t_line, t_cptr);

1449static void
1450declare_tokens(int assoc)
1451{
1452 int c;
1453 bucket *bp;
1454 Value_t value;
1455 char *tag = 0;
1456
1457 if (assoc != TOKEN)
1458 ++prec;
1459
1460 c = nextc();
1461 if (c == EOF)
1462 unexpected_EOF();
1463 if (c == '<')
1464 {
1465 tag = get_tag();
1466 c = nextc();
1467 if (c == EOF)
1468 unexpected_EOF();
1469 }
1470
1471 for (;;)
1472 {
1473 if (isalpha(UCH(c)) || c == '_' || c == '.' || c == '$')
1474 bp = get_name();
1475 else if (c == '\'' || c == '"')
1476 bp = get_literal();
1477 else
1478 return;
1479
1480 if (bp == goal)
1481 tokenized_start(bp->name);
1482 bp->class = TERM;
1483
1484 if (tag)
1485 {
1486 if (bp->tag && tag != bp->tag)
1487 retyped_warning(bp->name);
1488 bp->tag = tag;
1489 }
1490
1491 if (assoc != TOKEN)
1492 {
1493 if (bp->prec && prec != bp->prec)
1494 reprec_warning(bp->name);
1495 bp->assoc = (Assoc_t)assoc;
1496 bp->prec = prec;
1497 }
1498
1499 c = nextc();
1500 if (c == EOF)
1501 unexpected_EOF();
1502
1503 if (isdigit(UCH(c)))
1504 {
1505 value = get_number();
1506 if (bp->value != UNDEFINED && value != bp->value)
1507 revalued_warning(bp->name);
1508 bp->value = value;
1509 c = nextc();
1510 if (c == EOF)
1511 unexpected_EOF();
1512 }
1513 }
1514}

1516/*
1517 * %expect requires special handling
1518 * as it really isn't part of the yacc
1519 * grammar only a flag for yacc proper.
1520 */
1521static void
1522declare_expect(int assoc)
1523{
1524 int c;
1525
1526 if (assoc != EXPECT && assoc != EXPECT_RR)
1527 ++prec;
1528
1529 /*
1530 * Stay away from nextc - doesn't
1531 * detect EOL and will read to EOF.
1532 */
1533 c = *++cptr;
1534 if (c == EOF)
1535 unexpected_EOF();
1536
1537 for (;;)
1538 {
1539 if (isdigit(UCH(c)))
1540 {
1541 if (assoc == EXPECT)
1542 SRexpect = get_number();
1543 else
1544 RRexpect = get_number();
1545 break;
1546 }
1547 /*
1548 * Looking for number before EOL.
1549 * Spaces, tabs, and numbers are ok,
1550 * words, punc., etc. are syntax errors.
1551 */
1552 else if (c == '\n' || isalpha(UCH(c)) || !isspace(UCH(c)))
1553 {
1554 syntax_error(lineno, line, cptr);
1555 }
1556 else
1557 {
1558 c = *++cptr;
1559 if (c == EOF)
1560 unexpected_EOF();
1561 }
1562 }
1563}

1827/* set immediately prior to where copy_args() could be called, and incremented by
1828 the various routines that will rescan the argument list as appropriate */

1832static char *
1833copy_args(int *alen)
1834{
1835 struct mstring *s = msnew();
1836 int depth = 0, len = 1;
1837 char c, quote = 0;
1838 struct ainfo a;
1839
1840 a.a_lineno = lineno;
1841 a.a_line = dup_line();
1842 a.a_cptr = a.a_line + (cptr - line - 1);
1843
1844 while ((c = *cptr++) != R_PAREN || depth || quote)
1845 {
1846 if (c == ',' && !quote && !depth)
1847 {
1848 len++;
1849 mputc(s, 0);
1850 continue;
1851 }
1852 mputc(s, c);
1853 if (c == '\n')
1854 {
1855 get_line();
1856 if (!line)
1857 {
1858 if (quote)
1859 unterminated_string(&a);
1860 else
1861 unterminated_arglist(&a);
1862 }
1863 }
1864 else if (quote)
1865 {
1866 if (c == quote)
1867 quote = 0;
1868 else if (c == '\\')
1869 {
1870 if (*cptr != '\n')
1871 mputc(s, *cptr++);
1872 }
1873 }
1874 else
1875 {
1876 if (c == L_PAREN)
1877 depth++;
1878 else if (c == R_PAREN)
1879 depth--;
1880 else if (c == '\"' || c == '\'')
1881 quote = c;
1882 }
1883 }
1884 if (alen)
1885 *alen = len;
1886 FREE(a.a_line);
1887 return msdone(s);
1888}

1890static char *
1891parse_id(char *p, char **save)
1892{
1893 char *b;
1894
1895 while (isspace(UCH(*p)))
1896 if (*p++ == '\n')
1897 rescan_lineno++;
1898 if (!isalpha(UCH(*p)) && *p != '_')
1899 return NULL;
1900 b = p;
1901 while (IS_NAME2(UCH(*p)))
1902 p++;

1910static char *
1911parse_int(char *p, int *save)
1912{
1913 int neg = 0, val = 0;
1914
1915 while (isspace(UCH(*p)))
1916 if (*p++ == '\n')
1917 rescan_lineno++;
1918 if (*p == '-')
1919 {
1920 neg = 1;
1921 p++;
1922 }
1923 if (!isdigit(UCH(*p)))
1924 return NULL;
1925 while (isdigit(UCH(*p)))
1926 val = val * 10 + *p++ - '0';
1927 if (neg)
1928 val = -val;
1929 if (save)
1930 *save = val;
1931 return p;

1934static void
1935parse_arginfo(bucket *a, char *args, int argslen)
1936{
1937 char *p = args, *tmp;
1938 int i, redec = 0;
1939
1940 if (a->args >= 0)
1941 {
1942 if (a->args != argslen)
1943 arg_number_disagree_warning(rescan_lineno, a->name);
1944 redec = 1;
1945 }
1946 else
1947 {
1948 if ((a->args = argslen) == 0)
1949 return;
1950 a->argnames = TMALLOC(char *, argslen);
1951 NO_SPACE(a->argnames);
1952 a->argtags = TMALLOC(char *, argslen);
1953 NO_SPACE(a->argtags);
1954 }
1955 if (!args)
1956 return;
1957 for (i = 0; i < argslen; i++)
1958 {
1959 while (isspace(UCH(*p)))
1960 if (*p++ == '\n')
1961 rescan_lineno++;
1962 if (*p++ != '$')
1963 bad_formals();
1964 while (isspace(UCH(*p)))
1965 if (*p++ == '\n')
1966 rescan_lineno++;
1967 if (*p == '<')
1968 {
1969 havetags = 1;
1970 if (!(p = parse_id(p + 1, &tmp)))
1971 bad_formals();
1972 while (isspace(UCH(*p)))
1973 if (*p++ == '\n')
1974 rescan_lineno++;
1975 if (*p++ != '>')
1976 bad_formals();
1977 if (redec)
1978 {
1979 if (a->argtags[i] != tmp)
1980 arg_type_disagree_warning(rescan_lineno, i + 1, a->name);
1981 }
1982 else
1983 a->argtags[i] = tmp;
1984 }
1985 else if (!redec)
1986 a->argtags[i] = NULL;
1987 if (!(p = parse_id(p, &a->argnames[i])))
1988 bad_formals();
1989 while (isspace(UCH(*p)))
1990 if (*p++ == '\n')
1991 rescan_lineno++;
1992 if (*p++)
1993 bad_formals();
1994 }
1995 free(args);
1996}

1998static char *
1999compile_arg(char **theptr, char *yyvaltag)
2000{
2001 char *p = *theptr;
2002 struct mstring *c = msnew();
2003 int i, j, n;
2004 Value_t *offsets = NULL, maxoffset;
2005 bucket **rhs;
2006
2007 maxoffset = 0;
2008 n = 0;
2009 for (i = nitems - 1; pitem[i]; --i)
2010 {
2011 n++;
2012 if (pitem[i]->class != ARGUMENT)
2013 maxoffset++;
2014 }
2015 if (maxoffset > 0)
2016 {
2017 offsets = TMALLOC(Value_t, maxoffset + 1);
2018 NO_SPACE(offsets);
2019
2020 for (j = 0, i++; i < nitems; i++)
2021 if (pitem[i]->class != ARGUMENT)
2022 offsets[++j] = (Value_t)(i - nitems + 1);
2023 }
2024 rhs = pitem + nitems - 1;
2025
2026 if (yyvaltag)
2027 msprintf(c, "yyval.%s = ", yyvaltag);
2028 else
2029 msprintf(c, "yyval = ");
2030 while (*p)
2031 {
2032 if (*p == '$')
2033 {
2034 char *tag = NULL;
2035 if (*++p == '<')
2036 if (!(p = parse_id(++p, &tag)) || *p++ != '>')
2037 illegal_tag(rescan_lineno, NULL, NULL);
2038 if (isdigit(UCH(*p)) || *p == '-')
2039 {
2040 int val;
2041 if (!(p = parse_int(p, &val)))
2042 dollar_error(rescan_lineno, NULL, NULL);
2043 if (val <= 0)
2044 i = val - n;
2045 else if (val > maxoffset)
2046 {
2047 dollar_warning(rescan_lineno, val);
2048 i = val - maxoffset;
2049 }
2050 else if (maxoffset > 0)
2051 {
2052 i = offsets[val];
2053 if (!tag && !(tag = rhs[i]->tag) && havetags)
2054 untyped_rhs(val, rhs[i]->name);
2055 }
2056 msprintf(c, "yystack.l_mark[%d]", i);
2057 if (tag)
2058 msprintf(c, ".%s", tag);
2059 else if (havetags)
2060 unknown_rhs(val);
2061 }
2062 else if (isalpha(UCH(*p)) || *p == '_')
2063 {
2064 char *arg;
2065 if (!(p = parse_id(p, &arg)))
2066 dollar_error(rescan_lineno, NULL, NULL);
2067 for (i = plhs[nrules]->args - 1; i >= 0; i--)
2068 if (arg == plhs[nrules]->argnames[i])
2069 break;
2070 if (i < 0)
2071 unknown_arg_warning(rescan_lineno, "$", arg, NULL, NULL);
2072 else if (!tag)
2073 tag = plhs[nrules]->argtags[i];
2074 msprintf(c, "yystack.l_mark[%d]",
2075 i - plhs[nrules]->args + 1 - n);
2076 if (tag)
2077 msprintf(c, ".%s", tag);
2078 else if (havetags)
2079 untyped_arg_warning(rescan_lineno, "$", arg);
2080 }
2081 else
2082 dollar_error(rescan_lineno, NULL, NULL);
2083 }
2084 else if (*p == '@')
2085 {
2086 at_error(rescan_lineno, NULL, NULL);
2087 }
2088 else
2089 {
2090 if (*p == '\n')
2091 rescan_lineno++;
2092 mputc(c, *p++);
2093 }
2094 }
2095 *theptr = p;
2096 if (maxoffset > 0)
2097 FREE(offsets);
2098 return msdone(c);
2099}

2102can_elide_arg(char **theptr, char *yyvaltag)
2103{

2116 return 0;

2119 {
2120 n++;
2121 if (pitem[i]->class != ARGUMENT)

2135 if (isdigit(UCH(*p)) || *p == '-')

2160 for (i = plhs[nrules]->args - 1; i >= 0; i--)
2161 if (arg == plhs[nrules]->argnames[i])
2162 break;
2163 if (i >= 0)
2164 {
2165 if (!tag)
2166 tag = plhs[nrules]->argtags[i];
2167 rv = plhs[nrules]->args + n - i;
2168 }
2169 }

2171 {
2172 if (strcmp(tag, yyvaltag))
2173 rv = 0;
2174 }
2175 else if (tag || yyvaltag)
2176 rv = 0;

3017{
3018 char *code_text;
3019 int c;
3020 struct ainfo a;
3021 bucket *bp;
3022
3023 code_text = get_code(&a, "(*loc)");
3024

3026 {
3027 c = nextc();

3029 unexpected_EOF();
3030 if (c == '<')
3031 {
3032 if (cptr[1] == '>')
3033 { /* "no semantic type" default destructor */
3034 cptr += 2;
3035 if ((bp = default_destructor[UNTYPED_DEFAULT]) == NULL)
3036 {
3037 static char untyped_default[] = "<>";
3038 bp = make_bucket("untyped default");
3039 bp->tag = untyped_default;
3040 default_destructor[UNTYPED_DEFAULT] = bp;
3041 }
3042 if (bp->destructor != NULL)
3043 destructor_redeclared_warning(&a);
3044 else
3045 /* replace "$$" with "(*val)" in destructor code */
3046 bp->destructor = process_destructor_XX(code_text, NULL);
3047 }
3048 else if (cptr[1] == '*' && cptr[2] == '>')
3049 { /* "no per-symbol or per-type" default destructor */
3050 cptr += 3;
3051 if ((bp = default_destructor[TYPED_DEFAULT]) == NULL)
3052 {
3053 static char typed_default[] = "<*>";
3054 bp = make_bucket("typed default");
3055 bp->tag = typed_default;
3056 default_destructor[TYPED_DEFAULT] = bp;
3057 }
3058 if (bp->destructor != NULL)
3059 destructor_redeclared_warning(&a);
3060 else
3061 {
3062 /* postpone re-processing destructor $$s until end of grammar spec */
3063 bp->destructor = TMALLOC(char, strlen(code_text) + 1);
3064 NO_SPACE(bp->destructor);
3065 strcpy(bp->destructor, code_text);
3066 }
3067 }
3068 else
3069 { /* "semantic type" default destructor */
3070 char *tag = get_tag();
3071 bp = lookup_type_destructor(tag);
3072 if (bp->destructor != NULL)
3073 destructor_redeclared_warning(&a);
3074 else
3075 /* replace "$$" with "(*val).tag" in destructor code */
3076 bp->destructor = process_destructor_XX(code_text, tag);
3077 }
3078 }
3079 else if (isalpha(UCH(c)) || c == '_' || c == '.' || c == '$')
3080 { /* "symbol" destructor */
3081 bp = get_name();
3082 if (bp->destructor != NULL)
3083 destructor_redeclared_warning(&a);
3084 else
3085 {
3086 /* postpone re-processing destructor $$s until end of grammar spec */
3087 bp->destructor = TMALLOC(char, strlen(code_text) + 1);
3088 NO_SPACE(bp->destructor);
3089 strcpy(bp->destructor, code_text);
3090 }
3091 }
3092 else
3093 break;
3094 }
3095 free(a.a_line);
3096 free(code_text);
3097}

3508 max_tok_pval = symbol_pval[i];
3509 if (destructor)
3510 {
3511 symbol_destructor[i] = v[i]->destructor;
3512 symbol_type_tag[i] = v[i]->tag;
3513 }
3514#endif
3515 }
3516 symbol_name[start_symbol] = name_pool;
3517 symbol_value[start_symbol] = -1;
3518 symbol_prec[start_symbol] = 0;
3519 symbol_assoc[start_symbol] = TOKEN;
3520#if defined(YYBTYACC)
3521 symbol_pval[start_symbol] = (Value_t)(max_tok_pval + 1);
3522#endif
3523 for (++i; i < nsyms; ++i)
3524 {
3525 k = v[i]->index;
3526 symbol_name[k] = v[i]->name;
3527 symbol_value[k] = v[i]->value;
3528 symbol_prec[k] = v[i]->prec;
3529 symbol_assoc[k] = v[i]->assoc;
3530#if defined(YYBTYACC)
3531 symbol_pval[k] = (Value_t)((max_tok_pval + 1) + v[i]->value + 1);
3532 if (destructor)
3533 {
3534 symbol_destructor[k] = v[i]->destructor;
3535 symbol_type_tag[k] = v[i]->tag;
3536 }
3537#endif
3538 }
3539
3540 if (gflag)
3541 {
3542 symbol_pname = TMALLOC(char *, nsyms);
3543 NO_SPACE(symbol_pname);
3544
3545 for (i = 0; i < nsyms; ++i)
3546 protect_string(symbol_name[i], &(symbol_pname[i]));
3547 }
3548
3549 FREE(v);
3550}

3552static void
3553pack_grammar(void)
3554{
3555 int i;
3556 Value_t j;
3557 Assoc_t assoc;
3558 Value_t prec2;
3559
3560 ritem = TMALLOC(Value_t, nitems);
3561 NO_SPACE(ritem);
3562
3563 rlhs = TMALLOC(Value_t, nrules);
3564 NO_SPACE(rlhs);
3565
3566 rrhs = TMALLOC(Value_t, nrules + 1);
3567 NO_SPACE(rrhs);
3568
3569 rprec = TREALLOC(Value_t, rprec, nrules);
3570 NO_SPACE(rprec);
3571
3572 rassoc = TREALLOC(Assoc_t, rassoc, nrules);
3573 NO_SPACE(rassoc);
3574
3575 ritem[0] = -1;
3576 ritem[1] = goal->index;
3577 ritem[2] = 0;
3578 ritem[3] = -2;
3579 rlhs[0] = 0;
3580 rlhs[1] = 0;
3581 rlhs[2] = start_symbol;
3582 rrhs[0] = 0;
3583 rrhs[1] = 0;
3584 rrhs[2] = 1;
3585
3586 j = 4;
3587 for (i = 3; i < nrules; ++i)
3588 {
3589#if defined(YYBTYACC)
3590 if (plhs[i]->args > 0)
3591 {
3592 if (plhs[i]->argnames)
3593 {
3594 FREE(plhs[i]->argnames);
3595 plhs[i]->argnames = NULL;
3596 }
3597 if (plhs[i]->argtags)
3598 {
3599 FREE(plhs[i]->argtags);
3600 plhs[i]->argtags = NULL;
3601 }
3602 }
3603#endif /* defined(YYBTYACC) */
3604 rlhs[i] = plhs[i]->index;
3605 rrhs[i] = j;
3606 assoc = TOKEN;
3607 prec2 = 0;
3608 while (pitem[j])
3609 {
3610 ritem[j] = pitem[j]->index;
3611 if (pitem[j]->class == TERM)
3612 {
3613 prec2 = pitem[j]->prec;
3614 assoc = pitem[j]->assoc;
3615 }
3616 ++j;
3617 }
3618 ritem[j] = (Value_t)-i;
3619 ++j;
3620 if (rprec[i] == UNDEFINED)
3621 {
3622 rprec[i] = prec2;
3623 rassoc[i] = assoc;
3624 }
3625 }
3626 rrhs[i] = j;
3627
3628 FREE(plhs);
3629 FREE(pitem);
3630#if defined(YYBTYACC)
3631 clean_arg_cache();
3632#endif
3633}

3641

3676finalize_destructors(void)

3679 bucket *bp;

3683 {

3689 if ((bp = default_destructor[UNTYPED_DEFAULT]) != NULL)
3690 {
3691 symbol_destructor[i] = TMALLOC(char,
3692 strlen(bp->destructor) + 1);
3693 NO_SPACE(symbol_destructor[i]);

3695 }
3696 }
3697 else
3698 { /* use type destructor for this tag, if there is one */
3699 bp = lookup_type_destructor(tag);
3700 if (bp->destructor != NULL)
3701 {
3702 symbol_destructor[i] = TMALLOC(char,
3703 strlen(bp->destructor) + 1);
3704 NO_SPACE(symbol_destructor[i]);
3705 strcpy(symbol_destructor[i], bp->destructor);
3706 }
3707 else
3708 { /* use <*> destructor, if there is one */
3709 if ((bp = default_destructor[TYPED_DEFAULT]) != NULL)
3710 /* replace "$$" with "(*val).tag" in destructor code */
3711 symbol_destructor[i]
3712 = process_destructor_XX(bp->destructor, tag);
3713 }
3714 }
3715 }
3716 else
3717 { /* replace "$$" with "(*val)[.tag]" in destructor code */
3718 symbol_destructor[i]
3719 = process_destructor_XX(symbol_destructor[i], tag);
3720 }
3721 }
3722 /* 'symbol_type_tag[]' elements are freed by 'free_tags()' */
3723 DO_FREE(symbol_type_tag); /* no longer needed */
3724 if ((bp = default_destructor[UNTYPED_DEFAULT]) != NULL)
3725 {
3726 FREE(bp->name);
3727 /* 'bp->tag' is a static value, don't free */
3728 FREE(bp->destructor);
3729 FREE(bp);
3730 }
3731 if ((bp = default_destructor[TYPED_DEFAULT]) != NULL)
3732 {
3733 FREE(bp->name);
3734 /* 'bp->tag' is a static value, don't free */
3735 FREE(bp->destructor);
3736 FREE(bp);
3737 }
3738 if ((bp = default_destructor[TYPE_SPECIFIED]) != NULL)
3739 {
3740 bucket *p;
3741 for (; bp; bp = p)
3742 {
3743 p = bp->link;
3744 FREE(bp->name);
3745 /* 'bp->tag' freed by 'free_tags()' */
3746 FREE(bp->destructor);
3747 FREE(bp);
3748 }
3749 }
